race.comment: TA LA MASCA (7) improved effort at latest when third over 900m at Queanbeyan after being prominent at the corner. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. GOBINDA (4) turned in a modest performance when eighth last time out over 1200m at Wagga. That followed a win at Albury at the previous outing. Tackling a more suitable race and can play a big role. RAGER (2) turned in a nice effort to score two runs ago at Cooma. Couldn't follow that up last time out when ninth over 1300m at Orange. Finds the right race this time and can get the job done. HOLLERLOUD (6) looks to have found a suitable race today and won't be far away from the inside alley.
